# Building Custom Apps with VIB3+ SDK

## When to Use
- React/Vue/Flutter apps
- Custom input (touch, motion, gamepad)
- AR/XR applications

## Steps

### 1. Install
```bash
npm install vib34d-xr-quaternion-sdk
```

### 2. Initialize
```javascript
import { SensoryInputBridge, QuaternionFieldService, ShaderQuaternionSynchronizer } from 'vib34d-xr-quaternion-sdk';

const bridge = new SensoryInputBridge();
const fieldService = new QuaternionFieldService();
const sync = new ShaderQuaternionSynchronizer({
  bridge,
  fieldService,
  onSystemUpdate: (params) => {
    // params: {rot4dXY, rot4dXZ, rot4dYZ, rot4dXW, rot4dYW, rot4dZW}
  }
});
```

### 3. Connect Input
```javascript
bridge.publishPose(quaternion, position, confidence, source);
```

See: docs/atlases/vib3/sdk.md

# Common VIB3+ Tasks

## Add Animated Background
```html
<div style="position:fixed;inset:0;z-index:-1">
  <iframe src="https://domusgpt.github.io/vib3-plus-engine/?system=holographic&geometry=3&hue=280" style="width:100%;height:100%;border:none"></iframe>
</div>
<div style="position:relative;z-index:1">
  <!-- Your content -->
</div>
```

## Music Visualizer
Use `system=holographic` with `?audioEnabled=true`

## Cycle Geometries
```javascript
let geo = 0;
setInterval(() => {
  window.selectGeometry(geo);
  geo = (geo + 1) % 24;
}, 3000);
```

## Mouse Interaction
```javascript
document.addEventListener('mousemove', e => {
  const x = (e.clientX / innerWidth - 0.5) * 6.28;
  const y = (e.clientY / innerHeight - 0.5) * 6.28;
  window.updateParameter('rot4dXW', x);
  window.updateParameter('rot4dYW', y);
});
```
